In 12-inch skillet, cook bacon. Remove bacon and set aside; reserve dripping. In reserved drippings, cook onion and garlic in reserved drippings over medium-high heat, stirring occasionally, 3 minutes or until tender. Stir in flour, Lawry's(R) Seasoned Salt and pepper. Slowly add milk, stirring constantly. Bring to a boil and cook, stirring constantly, until thickened. Add spinach and bacon; heat through.